<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1465,1636]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1465,1492]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Ocellar tubercle with additional pair of setulae below ocellar setae; proclinate orbital seta nearer to inner vertical seta than to ptilinal fissure; palpus with hollow-shaped or depressed sense organ (modified from 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Chen" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="3951 - 3978" refId="ref33869" refString="Chen, H. W., Gao, J. J. &amp; Wen, S. Y. (2005 a) Species diversity of the genus Phortica Schiner in Yunnan, China, with descriptions of nine new species (Diptera, Drosophildae [sic]). Journal of Natural History, 39, 3951 - 3978. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930500533534" type="journal article" year="2005" yearSuffix="a">
Chen 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
. 2005a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1465,1636]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
